description:
The following discussion from !31649 should be addressed:

- [ ] @ealcantara started a [discussion](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/merge_requests/31649#note_343600513):  (+3 comments)

    > **suggestion**: We could completely remove this whole block and achieve the same results if we change the next one to:
    > 
    > ```scss
    >      &:not(:last-child) {
    >         @include gl-border-r-2;
    >         @include gl-border-r-solid;
    >         @include gl-border-white;
    >       }
    > ```
    > 
    > `gl-border-r-2` is not defined but we could follow the approach I described in https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/merge_requests/31649/diffs#note_343590724.

After implementing https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/217802, the `content` and `file_name` attributes might not be present in the call to the services. We need to ensure that if those params are not present then the `snippet_files` must be.

## Testing Activity

@fjsanpedro:
* Test that if not content & file_name is passed, snippet_files has to be present.

@vij:
* Test the param is required and raises an error accordingly

## MR Breakdown

@fjsanpedro:
* 1 MR - We just need to update the `valid_params?` method in the `Snippets::BaseService` to ensure that if the `file_name` and `content` are not present, then the `snippet_files` param has to be.

@vij:
 * We need to add conditional validation for `snippet_files` param
